{
  "stem": "1502.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "Jews had to wear a yellow star with a J in the middle.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "Jews could not walk after 8 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "There was a curfew on Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "My brother walked-- my brother got married during the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "His wife was from Antwerp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And he-- he went to-- while he was engaged to her, he went to see her, and came back to the train five minutes past 8:00.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "They arrested him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "They sent him to a concentration camp in a town called Breendonk, in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "Breendonk was a torture camp, mostly for Belgian underground people that they caught.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "It's still there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "It's a museum.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "And in [NON-ENGLISH], amongst the camps that-- that I mentioned, the main camps, Breendonk is also mentioned.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "In part, because, later on, when the Germans established the camp in Mechelen, that was part of the Breendonk complex.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "It was under the same commander.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the laws became stricter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my brother was arrested, and he spent five months in jail, in Antwerp, and six months in the torture camp of Breendonk.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was severely beaten.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People were buried alive in Breendonk.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a small camp, but very vicious.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A lot of people died there under torture.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Did they think your brother-in-law was involved with--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was my brother.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, absolutely not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because he was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because he was a Jew, and he violated the 8 o'clock curfew.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the laws became-- as we Jews started to get-- be very scared, when they heard these stories that people were taken to concentration camp for walking five minutes after curfew.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a very scary thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the laws became stricter and stricter on Jews, until-- that lasted until July, 1942.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "July, 1942, they decided to apply the-- the Wannsee final solution.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
